\begin_layout Section
The Maximum Circular Velocity Dependence of Halo Clustering
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this section, we investigate the maximum circular velocity dependence
 of halo clustering on both large and small scales.
 In order to do that, we compute correlation functions and measre halo biases
 for halo samples having different maximum circular velocities.
 We first describe how we select halos for each sample and then show how
 those samples have different clustering properties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As shown in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:vmax-mvir"

\end_inset

, the maximum circular velocity and halo mass has tight correlation, and
 yet the scatter between the maximum circular velocity and halo mass becomes
 larger with decreasing halo masses.
 In fact, we can compute an expected maximum circular velocity from halo
 mass
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
V_{{\rm max}}=0.465M_{{\rm vir}}^{1/3}\sqrt{G(\frac{4}{3}\pi\Delta_{{\rm h}}\rho_{{\rm crit}}\Omega_{m})^{1/3}\frac{c}{{\rm ln(1+c)-c/(1+c)}}},\label{eq:vmax-mvir}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{{\rm max}}$
\end_inset

 is the maximum circular velocity and 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{{\rm vir}}$
\end_inset

 is the halo mass, 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 is the gravitational constant, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta_{{\rm h}}$
\end_inset

 is XXX, and 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 is the concentration parameter.
 To obtain Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:vmax-mvir"

\end_inset

, we use the concentration of 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
{\rm log}_{10}c=-0.097{\rm log_{10}M_{vir}}+2.148.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

(??Ask Frank how he obtain this concentration value and why this is a reasonable
 value) 
\color black
In Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:vmax-mvir"

\end_inset

, this 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{{\rm max}}-M_{{\rm vir}}$
\end_inset

 relation with the above concentration (shown as a red solid line) intersects
 the peak of the distribution, which means that many of the halos follow
 this relation.
\end_layout

